.\" Manpage for simple_shell.


.TH man 1 "10 Nov 2021" "1.0" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter.

.SH SYNOPSIS
simple_shell [scripts] [command_string | file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple_shell is a command-line interpreter for Unix-like operating systems.It provides an interface for a computer user to the Unix/GNU Linux system so that the user can run different commands or utilities/tools with some input data. 


.SH OPTIONS
The simple_shell does not take any options. However, you can supply commands with options. 
Example
ls \- is a command that lists the directory  contents.
ls [OPTION]... [FILE]...

	-a, --all
              do not ignore entries starting with .

	-A, --almost-all
              do not list implied . and ..

	--author
              with -l, print the author of each file

.SH SEE ALSO
man bash

